            }
          },
          "_name": "content4",
          "_customHTML": "<section class=\"mbr-section content4\" group=\"Article\" data-bg-video=\"{{bg.type == 'video' && bg.value.url}}\" mbr-class=\"{'mbr-parallax-background': bg.parallax}\">\n\n    <mbr-parameters>\n    <!-- Block parameters controls (Blue \"Gear\" panel) -->\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"1\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"0\">\n\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Show Title\" name=\"showTitle\" checked>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Show Subtitle\" name=\"showSubtitle\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Show Buttons\" name=\"showButtons\">\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Background Color\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#2e2e2e\">\n    <!-- End block parameters -->\n    </mbr-parameters>\n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"media-container-row\">\n            <div class=\"title col-12 col-md-8\">\n                <h2 mbr-if=\"showTitle\" class=\"align-center pb-3 mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-2\"><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></h2>\n                <h3 mbr-if=\"showSubtitle\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-subtitle\" class=\"mbr-section-subtitle align-center mbr-light mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-5\">\n                    Shape your future web project with sharp design and refine coded functions.\n                </h3>\n                <div class=\"mbr-section-btn align-center py-4\" mbr-if=\"showButtons\" mbr-buttons mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\">\n                    <a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"https://mobirise.co\">LEARN MORE</a>\n                    <a class=\"btn btn-black-outline\" href=\"https://mobirise.co\">LIVE DEMO</a>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
          "_anchor": "content4-3d",
          "_isUserblock": true,
          "_sourceTheme": "mobirise4",
          "_cid": "rIiBIBGgmW",
          "_protectedParams": [],
          "_global": false,
          "_once": false,
          "_params": {}
        },
        {
          "alias": false,
          "_styles": {
            "padding-top": "(@paddingTop * 15px)",
            "padding-bottom": "(@paddingBottom * 15px)",
            "background-color": "@bgColor",
            ".counter-container": {
              "color": "#767676",
              "ol": {
                "margin-bottom": "0",
                "li": {
                  "margin-bottom": "1rem"
                },
                "& when (@stylizedCounters)": {
                  "counter-reset": "myCounter",
                  "li": {
                    "list-style": "none",
                    "padding-left": ".5rem",
                    "&:before": {
                      "position": "absolute",
                      "left": "0px",
                      "margin-top": "-10px",
                      "counter-increment": "myCounter",
                      "content": "counter(myCounter)",
                      "display": "inline-block",
                      "text-align": "center",
                      "margin": "5px 10px",
                      "line-height": "40px",
                      "transition": "all .2s",
                      "color": "contrast(@counterColor)",
                      "background": "@counterColor",
                      "width": "40px",
                      "height": "40px",
                      "border-radius": "50%",
                      "& when (@squareCounters)": {
                        "border-radius": "0"
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "_name": "content11",
          "_customHTML": "<section class=\"mbr-section article content11\">\n    <mbr-parameters>\n    <!-- Block parameters controls (Blue \"Gear\" panel) -->\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"4\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"4\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Stylized Counters\" name=\"stylizedCounters\" checked>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Square Counters\" name=\"squareCounters\" condition=\"stylizedCounters\">\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Counter Color\" name=\"counterColor\" value=\"#149dcc\" condition=\"stylizedCounters\">\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Background Color\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#ffffff\">\n    <!-- End block parameters -->\n    </mbr-parameters> \n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"media-container-row\">\n            <div class=\"mbr-text counter-container col-12 col-md-8 mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text\" data-multiline mbr-article>\n                <ol>\n                    <li><b>FILE FORMAT</b><br>All files must be a stereolithography file, with an STL extension (.STL)</li><li><b>PRINT VOLUME DIMENSIONS</b>\n <br>MakerGear M2 - 190 [X-AXIS] X 190MM [Y-AXIS] X 240MM [Z-AXIS]<br>Stratasys F270 - 305 [X-AXIS] X 254MM [Y-AXIS] X 254MM [Z-AXIS]<br>Stratasys F370 - 355 [X-AXIS] X 254MM [Y-AXIS] X 355MM [Z-AXIS]<br>Markforged Mark Two - 320 [X-AXIS] X 132MM [Y-AXIS] X 154MM [Z-AXIS]</li><li><b style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">FILAMENT TYPE - NO USER FILAMENT</b><b><br></b>MakerGear m2 printer uses PLA filament only<br>Stratasys F270 - ABS, PLA, ASA, PC-ABS, TPU 92A<br>Stratasys F370 - ABS, PLA, ASA, PC-ABS, TPU 92A<br>Markforged Mark Two - Carbon Fiber, Fiberglass, Kevlar, HSHT Fiberglass (High-Strength High-Temperature)</li><li><b style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">RESOLUTION, &nbsp;INFILL, &amp; PRINT SPEEDS</b><br>To help faciliate efficiency in time and aim towards low waste of materials all prints will be considered a rapid prototype and settings will be determined by the Lab Tech's discretion unless otherwise stated. &nbsp;If it is a structural print or a final print please let the Lab Tech's know of requested infill and resolution change. &nbsp;If you are not familiar with what settings you need speak with a lab tech.</li><li><b>MULTIPLE PARTS</b><br>If your model has multiple parts please seperate them all into their own .STL file.</li><li><b>HOW LONG WILL MY PRINT TAKE?</b><br>There are many factors that determine how long the print can take and is no definitive answer. &nbsp;To read about factors that can effect the time please see resouces here:<br><a href=\"https://3dprinterly.com/how-long-does-it-take-to-3d-print/#:~:targetText=So%20how%20long%20will%20it,take%20hours%20to%20several%20days.\" target=\"_blank\">3Dprinterly.com Article</a><br><a href=\"https://3space.com/blog/how-long-does-3d-printing-take/\" target=\"_blank\">3Space.com Article with picture examples</a><br><br>To give a rough example (again all dependent on model, speed, infill, resolution, layer height, skirt, raft, brim, wall thickness etc) one lego may take approximately 4 minutes, a cell phone case - 20 minutes, baseball with 15% infill - 2 hours, tesla coil holder - 6-12 hours, transmission case (15 x 10 x 5) - multiple days. &nbsp;Previous years ECE robot bumpers could take upwards to 14 hours depending. &nbsp;Again this is rough estimates.<br><br>Other considerations to account for are failed prints. &nbsp;We have had it before where a print can go perfectly for 10 hours and have layer separation right at the end. &nbsp;Additionally, improper model designs can greatly effect printing such as too tight of tolerances, walls not being thick enough, empty walls etc.<br><br>Also, if there are other prints waiting to be printed before yours it can take up to a week or two before yours will be printed.</li><li><b style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">PRINTING RESTRICTIONS&nbsp;<br></b>We reserve the right to refuse any requests that are: <br><br>- Complicated prints with very tight tolerances <br>- Prints that are not designed correctly<br>- Prohibitied by local, state, or federal law <br>- Unsafe, dangerous, or pose a threat to the well being of others <br>- Offensive or inappropriate content &nbsp;<br>- Intended for resale</li></ol><ol>\n                </ol>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
          "_cid": "rIiPpL1r7c",
          "_anchor": "content11-3l",
