        {
          "alias": false,
          "_styles": {
            "padding-top": "(@paddingTop * 15px)",
            "padding-bottom": "(@paddingBottom * 15px)",
            "background-color": "@bgColor",
            ".line": {
              "background-color": "@lineColor",
              "color": "@lineColor",
              "align": "center",
              "height": "2px",
              "margin": "0 auto"
            },
            ".section-text": {
              "padding": "2rem 0",
              "text-align": "left",
              "color": "#232323"
            },
            ".inner-container": {
              "margin": "0 auto"
            },
            "@media (max-width: 768px)": {
              ".inner-container": {
                "width": "100% !important"
              }
            }
          },
          "_name": "content9",
          "_customHTML": "<section class=\"mbr-section article content9\" group=\"Article\">\n    \n    <mbr-parameters>\n    <!-- Block parameters controls (Blue \"Gear\" panel) -->\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"2\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"8\" step=\"1\" value=\"1\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Text Width\" name=\"innerWidth\" min=\"50\" max=\"100\" step=\"1\" value=\"100\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Line Width\" name=\"lineLength\" min=\"10\" max=\"100\" step=\"1\" value=\"25\">\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Line Color\" name=\"lineColor\" value=\"#149dcc\">\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Background Color\" name=\"bgColor\" value=\"#ffffff\">\n    <!-- End block parameters -->\n    </mbr-parameters> \n\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"inner-container\" mbr-style=\"{'width': innerWidth + '%'}\">\n            <hr class=\"line\" mbr-style=\"{'width': lineLength + '%'}\">\n            <div class=\"section-text align-center mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" data-app-selector=\".section-text\" mbr-text><p>- &nbsp; &nbsp;Ansys offers educational student versions of their software. &nbsp;ANSYS Student is their ANSYS Workbench-based bundle of ANSYS Mechanical, ANSYS CFD, ANSYS Autodyn, ANSYS SpaceClaim, and ANSYS DesignXplorer. ANSYS Student is used by hundreds of thousands of students globally. &nbsp;It is a great choice if you are already familiar with the ANSYS Workbench platform.&nbsp;<br></p><p>To download please goto <a href=\"https://www.ansys.com/academic/free-student-products\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ansys.com/academic/free-student-products</a> and click the ANSYS Student picture and then click <b>DOWNLOAD ANSYS STUDENT 2019 Rx</b> button.</p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><b>INSTALLATION</b><br></span><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><br>Before Installing:&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">- Ensure that your computer meets the technical requirements necessary to run the software. Please see the <b><a href=\"https://www.ansys.com/-/media/ansys/corporate/files/pdf/solutions/it-professionals/platform-support/ansys-platform-support-strategy-plans-january-2019.pdf?la=en\" target=\"_blank\">platform support document</a></b> for details\n<br></span><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">- Ensure that you have administrator privileges for the computer on which you are installing this product&nbsp;<br></span><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">- Uninstall any existing ANSYS products present on your comptuer. The ANSYS Student installation will orverwrite any existing installations&nbsp;<br></span><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">- Please visit the <a href=\"https://studentcommunity.ansys.com/\">ANSYS Student Community</a> for additional assistance</span></p>Installation Steps for the ANSYS Student Products from Release 18.0 onward:<br>- Extract (unzip) the downloaded installation files\n<div>- Right-click on setup.exe and select Run as Administrator. (This will run setup.exe from the the extracted files.)\n</div><div>- Read and accept the clickwrap to continue\n</div><div>- Click the right arrow button to accept the default values throughout the installation\n</div><div>- Click the exit button to close the installer\n</div><div>- The ANSYS Student software is now installed. Congratulations!\n</div><div>- Reboot your machine and then run the ANSYS Student product form your Start menu by selecting Workbench 18.0 (Or corresponding version number)\n</div><div>- To view System and Browser Requirements, Problem Size Limits, License Duration, What's Included, and Prior Release information click the corresponding tab links on the same page</div></div>\n            <hr class=\"line\" mbr-style=\"{'width': lineLength + '%'}\">\n        </div>\n        </div>\n</section>",
          "_cid": "rIbW1x2taw",
          "_anchor": "content9-1c",
          "_protectedParams": [],
          "_global": false,
          "_once": false,
          "_params": {}
